{"expireTime":9007200804686261000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-89ee18455b2603c12e04c6dcc8941802-gatsby-remark-graphvizgatsby-remark-code-titlesgatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-autolink-headersgatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypants-","val":"<h1 id=\"gatsby-plugin-remove-trailing-slashes\"><a href=\"#gatsby-plugin-remove-trailing-slashes\" aria-label=\"gatsby plugin remove trailing slashes permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>gatsby-plugin-remove-trailing-slashes</h1>\n<p>This plugin removes trailing slashes from your project’s paths. For\nexample, <code class=\"language-text\">yoursite.com/about/</code> becomes <code class=\"language-text\">yoursite.com/about</code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"important-considerations\"><a href=\"#important-considerations\" aria-label=\"important considerations permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Important considerations</h2>\n<p>This plugin is intended to remove trailing slashes from paths generated by Gatsby itself.</p>\n<p>This however does not prevent the resolution of pages that have trailing slashes, due to the way browsers are built to interpret URLs as paths.</p>\n<p>This means that a user will need to take the extra step of ensuring that all router links direct towards paths that do not end in a slash.</p>\n<p>For example, <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Link to=&quot;/about/&quot;&gt;</code> will render the view related to <code class=\"language-text\">/about</code> but will display as <code class=\"language-text\">/about/</code> in the browsers address bar.</p>\n<p>This is an important factor when relying on path driven logic, such as in the use case of the <code class=\"language-text\">Link</code> components <code class=\"language-text\">activeClassName</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">activeStyle</code> props.</p>\n<p>For example, if the current route is <code class=\"language-text\">/about</code>, the component <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Link to=&quot;/about/&quot; activeStyle={{ color: &#39;rebeccapurple&#39; }}&gt;</code> wouldn’t match because of the slash.</p>\n<h4 id=\"netlify-trailing-slashes\"><a href=\"#netlify-trailing-slashes\" aria-label=\"netlify trailing slashes permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Netlify Trailing Slashes</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.netlify.com\">Netlify</a> users should also take into account that that the service will match paths to redirect rules regardless of whether or not they contain a trailing slash, potentially causing infinite redirect loops and unexpected behaviours.</p>\n<p>This can be negated through the use of their Pretty URL feature, which rewrites URLs to pretty URLs.</p>\n<p>Please see the Netlify docs for more information:\n<a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/docs/redirects/#trailing-slash\">https://www.netlify.com/docs/redirects/#trailing-slash</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"usage\"><a href=\"#usage\" aria-label=\"usage permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Usage</h2>\n<p>Install:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm install --save-dev gatsby-plugin-remove-trailing-slashes</code></pre></div>\n<p>Then configure via <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-config.js</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">...</span>\n  plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">...</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-plugin-remove-trailing-slashes`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>That’s it.</p>"}